===Etymology===
Sino-Tibetan: {{cog|bo|རུ་མ||curdled milk}}, {{cog|kac||ru<sup>31</sup>-|liquor}}. Similar-looking words in Tai-Kadai may be Han or post-Han loans; cf. {{cog|tai-pro|*ʰlawꟲ||liquor}} ({{cog|th|เหล้า}}) ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Compare also {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*raːwʔ}}, whence {{cog|vi|rượu}}, {{cog|mtq|-}} Bi {{m|mtq|rão}}, {{cog|tou|-}} [Cuối Chăm] ''riɛw⁴'', Proto-Pong ''*riɛw⁴'', as well as {{cog|th|เหล้า|t=liquor}}.

